http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/Addepalli-remembered/article14004760.ece

Underscoring the need for bringing out a compilation with the best poetry of renowned poet Addepalli Ramamohana Rao, poet and literary critic Sannidhanam Narasimha Sarma on Sunday said that though a good number of volumes of poetry penned by the late Addepalli were available in the market, a compilation with the best works was the need of the hour.Strike a balanceAddressing a meeting organised by city-based Aswadana Sahithi Samithi to commemorate the late Addepalli Rama Mohana Rao at Gandhi Bhavan here, Mr. Sarma said that the late Addepalli was successful in striking a balance between traditional and modern poetry.